    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nLet's take this one step at a time! Click the arrow to expand the step when you're ready.\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">1. Add a <code>Painter</code> parameter to the functions</span>]\r\nLook at the `take_three_paint()` and `paint_three()` functions near the top of the code.\r\n\r\nEach function is missing a parameter. Add `this_painter` inside the parentheses so each function knows which `Painter` it should use.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">2. Update both functions to use the parameter</span>]\r\nInside the functions, replace `fiona` and `selena` with `this_painter`.\r\n\r\nThis change makes your code reusable for any `Painter` you pass into the function.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">3. Call the functions with <code>fiona</code> as the argument</span>]\r\nScroll through the code and look for the `TODO`s that call the functions with `fiona`.\r\n\r\nInstead of writing out every step, replace the code with calls to `take_three_paint(fiona)` and `paint_three(fiona)`.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">4. Call the functions with <code>selena</code> as the argument</span>]\r\nNow look for the `TODO`s where the functions should be used with `selena`.\r\n\r\nReplace the repeated lines where `selena` takes paint or paints with calls to your updated functions: `take_three_paint(selena)` and `paint_three(selena)`.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/f496b9310f332da74d1ccf289cf0f220-choiceC.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo make your function flexible, use a parameter like `this_painter` so the function works with any `Painter` you choose.\r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef paint_line(this_painter):\r\n  this_painter.take_paint()\r\n  this_painter.paint(\"white\")\r\n  this_painter.move()\r\n\r\npaint_line(south_side_painter)\r\n```",
